Following ANO, daily blocks are identified as contiguous 2-D spatial signatures with anomalies above a given threshold (the same as in ANO). Similar to ABS, these areas are also required to be associated with meridional Z500 gradient reversals around a reference latitude (ϕc), defined for each longitude and calendar month as the latitude with maximum variance in the 5-day high-pass Z500 filtered field. This condition is demanded by computing the difference between ∆-width latitudinal averages of Z500:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
